definitions.definition: To place an object over another object, usually in such a way that both will be visible.
examples: He superimposed the company logo over the image.

definitions.definition: To establish a structural system over, independently of underlying structures.

main_definition: To place an object over another object, usually in such a way that both will be visible.
secondary_definitions: ( geology ) To establish a structural system over, independently of underlying structures.
